  json('[{"engine":"B58 Gen1 has no fundamental design flaws. Issues are age/maintenance-related gasket and plastic component degradation, not design flaws. OFHG and coolant are predictable progressive failures. vs N63 (62): no hot-vee turbo heat, no engine-out timing chain, no valve stem seal oil consumption. +23 vs N63 is justified by EngineScope 93 vs 42 ratings and drastically lower repair costs","transmission":"Same proven ZF 8HP50 as 750i. One of the best automatics in the industry, generally reliable to 150K+ mi with fluid changes","chassis":"Same air suspension, same Carbon Core body as 750i. IB brake recall applies to all G11. Air spring leaks are age/mileage related","electronics":"Same iDrive (ID5), same Gesture Control, same DSC module as 750i. Fewer engine management sensors than N63 (single turbo vs twin, no cylinder deactivation). Display key is a known weak point. LCI gets ID6 with more complexity","ease_of_repair":"B58 I6 is FAR more accessible than N63 V8 - no engine-out jobs for timing chain or valve stem seals. OFHG and cooling jobs are standard labor. Still a 7 Series (low volume, tight bay) so parts availability harder than 3/5 Series. +14 vs N63 (46) reflects accessibility gain"}]')
